Sentencas: The cathode is a critical component in the utilization of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) technique.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+δ with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase as an advanced cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, the perovskite oxide SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+delta (SBCCC) with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase was proposed as an advanced cathode material of SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+δ with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase as an advanced cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is synthesized through a simple sol-gel method and displays a good chemical and thermal matching with Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 electrolyte, high electrocatalytic activity and durability to the oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+δ with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase as an advanced cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Its thermal expansion coefficient is 14.3 x 10(-6)degrees C-1, which is very close to that of Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 electrolyte (11.5 x 10(-6)degrees C-1).
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+δ with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase as an advanced cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area-specific resistance low to 0.076 Omega cm(2) (700 degrees C) and output power density high to 1.23 W cm(-2) (800 degrees C) were obtained for the SBCCC-based symmetrical and single cells.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+δ with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase as an advanced cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A stable and non-attenuating output current density was acquired for the SBCCC-based single-cell working at 750 degrees C and 0.7 V for 200 h. These results demonstrate that SBCCC with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase is an attractive electrocatalyst for SOFC application.
Titulo: Characterization of SmBa0.5Ca0.5CoCuO5+δ with exsolved CaCuO2-type phase as an advanced cathode material of solid oxide fuel cells
